The paper deals with capacity achieving decoders for fingerprinting and group testing, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses decoding schemes for large coalitions, which involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of joint decoders and the analysis of asymptotics suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and statistics (cs.SI).
